.TH "ppc4xx_edac_map_dcrs" 9 "ppc4xx_edac_map_dcrs" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ppc4xx_edac_map_dcrs \- locate and map controller registers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ppc4xx_edac_map_dcrs
.BI "(const struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "dcr_host_t *dcr_host "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "np" 12
A pointer to the device tree node containing the DCR
resources to map.
.IP "dcr_host" 12
A pointer to the DCR data to populate with the
DCR mapping.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine attempts to locate in the device tree and map the DCR
register resources associated with the controller's indirect DCR
address and data windows.

Returns 0 if the DCRs were successfully mapped; otherwise, < 0 on
error.
